              "acceptedAnswer": {
                "@type": "Answer",
                "text": "Single-story homes often start around $180–250. Price depends on roof size, number of stories, access, and any add-ons. We confirm the total price before we begin."
              }
            },
            {
              "@type": "Question",
              "name": "What is included in a standard gutter cleaning visit?",
              "acceptedAnswer": {
                "@type": "Answer",
                "text": "A standard gutter cleaning visit usually includes debris removal from gutters, basic downspout flow check, cleanup of the work area, and photo proof on request. We confirm the scope before we start."
              }
            },
            {
              "@type": "Question",
              "name": "Do clogged gutters cause roof leaks?",
              "acceptedAnswer": {
                "@type": "Answer",
                "text": "Yes, clogged gutters can eventually lead to roof leaks. When gutters are blocked with leaves, moss, and debris, rainwater cannot flow away properly. Water begins to overflow and can get under shingles or behind the fascia. Over time this moisture may damage the roof structure, siding, and even the foundation of the home. Regular gutter cleaning helps prevent these problems and keeps water draining safely away from your house."
              }
            },
            {
              "@type": "Question",
              "name": "Do you work in rain or winter?",
              "acceptedAnswer": {
                "@type": "Answer",
                "text": "We avoid heavy rain or snow for safety and to prevent mess. In winter, we usually work on dry days and above-freezing temperatures."
              }
            },
            {
              "@type": "Question",
              "name": "Do you clean windows inside and outside?",
              "acceptedAnswer": {
                "@type": "Answer",
                "text": "Yes. We can do exterior-only or both interior and exterior. We can also include sliding doors and sills if agreed in advance."
              }
            },
            {
              "@type": "Question",
              "name": "Is roof moss removal safe for my roof?",
              "acceptedAnswer": {
                "@type": "Answer",
                "text": "Yes. We use safe methods and avoid harsh approaches that damage shingles. When possible, we minimize roof foot traffic."
              }
            },
            {
              "@type": "Question",
              "name": "Do you provide before/after photos?",
              "acceptedAnswer": {
                "@type": "Answer",
                "text": "Yes, on request. Many homeowners love photo proof, especially for gutters and roof work, so you can clearly see the result."
              }
            },
            {
              "@type": "Question",
              "name": "How do bookings and payments work?",
              "acceptedAnswer": {
                "@type": "Answer",
                "text": "Request a quote or call us. We confirm the price and schedule. Payment is after the job (cash, e-Transfer, or card). No deposit required."
              }
            },
            {
              "@type": "Question",
              "name": "What areas do we serve?",
